reviewText: it never let me see the show but maybe 5 or 10 mins of it  also jamened up my player  it still jammed

The Final Frolics of Mr. Bean is ingenious, as are pretty much all of the Mr. Bean episodes.  Rowan Atkinson is, as always, absolutely hilarious, and the scriptwriters are certified geniuses in my book.

This item is worth every penny.  I won't give away much about it, except to tell you that you especially don't want to miss the episode where Mr. Bean chases a golf ball all over town.

No-no. Apart from the sketch in the laundry, this tape is simply not funny. The minigolf sketch contains ONE joke... which is repeated 20 times, and the hospital and Queen's guard sketches are below mediocre. Goodbye, Mr Bean.
